dcterms:description: The Multi-dimensional Knapsack Problem (MKP) consists of multiple inequality constraints and is a variant of the 0-1 knapsack problem. The aim is to find a subset of items that leads to maximum profit without exceeding any of the capacities.
dcterms:title: Multi-dimensional Knapsack Problem (MKP)

dcterms:description: The Quadratic Assignment Problem (QAP) involves assigning a set of facilities to a set of locations while minimizing the total cost based on distances and flows between facilities.
dcterms:title: Quadratic Assignment Problem (QAP)

dcterms:creator: Gerhard Reinelt
dcterms:description: The Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP) involves finding the shortest possible route that visits each city exactly once and returns to the origin city.
dcterms:title: Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP)
